 cultures that defined the age, seems to have implicitly reformulated its entire literary system in the context of the imminent breakdown of the old courtly world, as Turkish power expanded and redefined the landscape.  Through close readings of a little-known corpus of texts from eastern India, this ambitious book demonstrates how a local and rural sensibility came to infuse the cosmopolitan language of Sanskrit, creating a regional literary idiom that would define the emergence of the Bengali language and its literary traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPoeticsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSanskrit poetryxHistory and criticism. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  a13th century literature.  abangladesh.  abengal.  abengali language.  abookish.  acosmopolitan.  acourtly writing.  acreative writing.  acultural studies.  aeastern india.  ahigh literature.  ahigh styles of writing.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  aindian subcontinent.  aking laksmanasena of bengal.  aliterary studies.  aliterary traditions.  aliterary.  aliterature.  alow styles of writing.  aold courtly world.  apastoral poetry.  apoems.  apoetry and poets.  apoetry.  aregional literature.  arural.  asanskrit poetry.  aurban.  averse.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028205640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095779440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957794423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957794/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-064977-2